dafsNicState.syntax: INTEGER {up(1), -- ready to pass packetsdown(2),testing(3) -- in some test mode}

userDefined.desc: A polling-style trap built using the 'snmp traps'command on the filer.

dhmNoticeDegradedIO.desc: Disk Health Monitor -Reported a Disk Degraded-I/O Event

dhmNoticePFAEvent.desc: Disk Health Monitor -Reported a Disk Predictive-Failure Event

emergencyTrap.desc: A user-defined trap indicating an extremely urgentsituation, usually indicating that the system hasfailed and is shutting down.

alertTrap.desc: A user-defined trap indicating a condition thatshould be corrected immediately, such as a failed disk.

criticalTrap.desc: A user-defined trap indicating a critical condition,such as a hard device error.

errorTrap.desc: A user-defined trap indicating an error condition,such as a mistake in a configuration file.

warningTrap.desc: A user-defined trap indicating a condition whichis not an error, but which may require special handling.

notificationTrap.desc: A user-defined trap meant to provide notification,such as an hourly uptime message.

informationalTrap.desc: A user-defined trap used for informational purposes.

dbgTrap.desc: A user-defined trap used for debugging purposes.This trap was previously mis-documented as being trapnumber 17, with the name debugTrap. It has always,actually, been trap 18. The name change is to avoidissues with environments that already have a recordfor debugTrap.

diskFailedShutdown.desc: System is shutting down because the system has beenrunning in degraded mode for 24 hours.The trap includes a string describing the failed disk.

diskFailed.desc: One or more disks failed.The trap includes a string describing the failed disk(s).

diskRepaired.desc: The failed disks have been repaired.This trap is a placeholder -it is not currently sent by Data ONTAP.

fanFailureShutdown.desc: Critical chassis or cpu fans have failed and the systemis shutting down.

fanFailed.desc: One or more chassis fans failed.The trap includes a string describing the failed fan(s).

fanWarning.desc: One or more chassis or cpu fans are in warning state.The trap includes a string describing the fan(s) inthe warning state.

powerSupplyFailureShutdown.desc: Critical power supplies or power rails failed andthe system is shutting down.

powerSupplyFailed.desc: One or more redundant power supplies failed.Include in the trap a string describingthe failed power supply(ies).

powerSupplyWarning.desc: One or more power supplies or power rails inwarning state. Include in the trap a string describingthe power supply(ies) or the power rail(s) in thewarning state.

powerSupplyRepaired.desc: Previously-failed power supplies or power rails have beenrepaired.

cpuTooBusy.desc: CPU utilization exceeds 90%.This trap is not enabled by default.To enable this trap set the registryentry options.monitor.cpu.enable to on.Note that as the threshold for this trap ischecked once a minute it is possible to receivemultiple instances of this trap in a short time.

cpuOk.desc: CPU utilization has dropped back below 90%.This trap is a placeholder -it is not currently sent by Data ONTAP.

nvramBatteryDischarged.desc: The NVRAM battery is fully discharged.

nvramBatteryLow.desc: The charge in the NVRAM battery is low.

clusterNodeFailed.desc: A node in a Cluster FailOver configuration failed.Its partner will assume service for the failed node.

clusterNodeTakenOver.desc: The partner has taken over for a failed cluster node.

clusterNodeRepaired.desc: A cluster node has resumed operation.

volumeFull.desc: At least one volume is more than 98% full.The string sent with the trap gives thename of the volume or volumes which exceedthe volumeFull or volumeNearlyFull thresholds

volumeNearlyFull.desc: At least one volume is more than 95% full.The string sent with the trap gives thename of the volume or volumes which exceedthe volumeFull or volumeNearlyFull thresholds

volumeRepaired.desc: All volumes are now under 95% full.

volumesStillFull.desc: At least one volume that was full or nearly full is now OK,but more volumes still exceed the volumeNearlyFull orvolumeFull thresholds. This trap is generally sent withina short time of when a volume becomes OK, though if twovolumes become OK within this timeframe, only one trap issent. The string sent with the trap gives the name of thevolume or volumes which still exceed the volumeFull orvolumeNearlyFull thresholds. It does not send the name ofany volume that is OK.

overTempShutdown.desc: System temperature is too high to continueoperating. The system is shutting down.

overTemp.desc: System temperature is too high and in thewarning level.

overTempRepaired.desc: System temperature has returned to anacceptable value.

shelfFault.desc: A disk storage shelf reported a fault, probably dueto a problem with drive placement, fans, power,or temperature.

shelfRepaired.desc: A previously-reported shelf fault is now corrected.

globalStatusNonRecoverable.desc: The appliance's overall status changed to'nonRecoverable', indicating a problem so severethat the appliance is shutting down.

globalStatusCritical.desc: The appliance's overall status changed to 'critical',indicating a problem that needs immediate attention.

globalStatusNonCritical.desc: The appliance's overall status changed to 'nonCritical',indicating a problem that needs attention.

globalStatusOk.desc: The appliance's overall status returned to normal.

softQuotaExceeded.desc: A user has exceeded their soft quota limit.

softQuotaNormal.desc: A user is safely back under their soft quota limit.

autosupportSendError.desc: Unable to send autosupport.The trap includes a string describing the reason for the failure.

autosupportConfigurationError.desc: Autosupport may be configured incorrectly.The trap includes a string describing the mis-configuration.

upsLinePowerOff.desc: UPS: Input line power has failed and UPS is now on battery.

upsBatteryCritical.desc: UPS: Battery is nearly exhausted, starting graceful shutdown.

upsShuttingDown.desc: UPS: Shutting down now: Time left on battery is exhuasted.

upsBatteryWarning.desc: UPS: Warning: Time left on battery is getting critical.

upsLinePowerRetored.desc: UPS: Input line power has been restored and UPS is now off battery.

appEmergency.desc: The application encountered an extremely urgentsituation and requires an immediate response.

appAlert.desc: The application is in a condition that shouldbe corrected immediately.

appCritical.desc: The application encountered a critical condition.

appError.desc: The application encountered an error condition.

appWarning.desc: The application is in a condition which is not anerror, but which may require special handling.

appNotice.desc: The application is notifing of a certain event.

appInfo.desc: The application's message is meant for informationalpurposes.

appTrap.desc: The application requires to be debugged.

alfFilewrap.desc: The internal audit file has wrapped. You are currently losing eventrecords. Warning the user.

alfFileSaved.desc: The internal audit log has been autosaved to an external evt file.Notifying the user.

alfFileNearlyFull.desc: The internal audit log file is nearly full. The file is going towrap. Notifying the user.

quotaExceeded.desc: One of the quota limits has been exceeded.The trap includes a string describing the specific eventwhich triggered the trap. The string is structuredin the following form:Quota Event: status=exceeded, type={hard|soft|threshold},user={username}, volume={volume}, limit_item={files|disk},limit_value={#files|#kilobytes}[ , treeid={tree-id} ] [ , vfiler={vfiler} ]An example of a complete message would be:Quota Event: status=exceeded, type=soft,user=admin, volume=vol1, limit_item=disk, limit_value=1000000,treeid=8Additional key=value items may, in the future, be appendedto this message.

quotaNormal.desc: One of the quota limits has gone back down to a normal level.The trap includes a string describing the specific eventwhich triggered the trap. The string is structuredin the following form:Quota Event: status=normal, type={hard|soft|threshold},user={username}, volume={volume}, limit_item={files|disk},limit_value={#files|#kilobytes}[ , treeid={tree-id} ] [ , vfiler={vfiler} ]An example of a complete message would be:Quota Event: status=normal, type=soft,user=admin, volume=vol1, limit_item=disk, limit_value=1000000,treeid=8Additional key=value items may, in the future, be appendedto this message.

waflDirNearlyFull.desc: The directory has surpassed 90% of its sub-directory limit.The priority of waflDirFull and this trap are out of orderfor backwards compatibility.

waflDirFull.desc: The directory has reached its sub-directory limit

eccSummary.desc: Memory ECC: number of new correctable ECC errors

eccMasked.desc: Memory ECC: High frequency of ECC errors

ftpdMaxConnNotice.desc: Ftp daemon: number of connections hits maximum number

ftpdMaxConnThresholdNotice.desc: Ftp daemon: number of connections nearly hits maximum number

scsitgtFCPLinkBreak.desc: SCSI Target: Link Break on FCP adapter

scsitgtPartnerPathMisconfigured.desc: SCSI Target: FCP Partner Path Misconfigured

scsitgtThrottleNotice.desc: SCSI Target: Throttle limit event notification

vifPrimaryLinkFailed.desc: Vif: The primary Interface on a Single mode vif has failed

vifAllLinksFailed.desc: Vif: All the links of the vif have failed

vscanVirusDetectedError.desc: VScan: A virus scanner has detected a virus on the Filer

vscanDisConnection.desc: VScan: A virus scanner has dropped its connection from the Filer

vscanConfigurationChange.desc: VScan: There has been a change to the vscan configuration

vscanConnection.desc: VScan: A virus scanner has made a connection to the Filer

vscanServerUpgrade.desc: VScan: The Vscan server has been upgraded

volumeRestrictedByMirrorBigIo.desc: A volume that experienced a medium error during reconstructionis restricted and marked wafl-inconsistent, but startingwafliron has failed. This trap is issued to alert operatorthat a volume is not accessible and wafliron must be startedto allow access to it.

volumeInconsistentUmount.desc: This trap is issued when we unmount a volume due to aninconsistency.

volumeStateChanged.desc: Volume is being taken offline or being restricted.The string sent with trap specifies name of affected volumeand its state.

volumeOnline.desc: Volume is online now. The string sent with trap specifiesname of volume which is online now.

rmcCardNeedsReplacement.desc: Remote Management Controller card needs replacement. The trapincludes a string specifying the reason for replacement

rmcCardMissingCables.desc: Remote Management Controller card is missing its internalcable, or LAN cable or power supply cable. The trap includesa string specifing the missing component.

volumeRemoteUnreachable.desc: Local volume encountered an error while communicatingto remote volume.

volumeRemoteOk.desc: The communication between remote volume and local volumereturned to normal.

volumeRemoteRestored.desc: The data on remote volume has been fully restored to localvolume.

volumeRemoteRestoreBegin.desc: The data on remote volume has started being restored to localvolume by Restore-on-Demand.

volumeRestrictedRootConflict.desc: Volume is restricted due to a root volume conflict. Thestring sent with trap specifies name of conflicting volumewhich is being restricted.

volumeOfflineTooBig.desc: Volume can not be brought online because its raw size islarger than maximum allowed size. The string sent with trapspecifies name of affected volume and its raw size, andmaximum allowed size.

volumeOffline.desc: Volume is being taken offline. The string sent with trapspecifies name of affected volume and reason for beingtaken offline.

volumeRestricted.desc: Volume is being restricted. The string sent with trapspecifies name of affected volume and reason for beingrestricted.

volumeDegradedDirty.desc: Volume is degraded and has dirty parity. WAFL_check must berun on this volume before it can be brought online. The stringsent with trap specifies name of affected volume.

volumeError.desc: This trap is issued when a volume can not be brought onlinedue to an error. The string sent with trap specifies name ofaffected volume and error description.

snapmirrorSyncFailed.desc: Synchronous SnapMirror failed and went into asynchronous mode.

snapmirrorSyncOk.desc: Synchronous SnapMirror went into synchronous mode.

chassisTemperatureShutdown.desc: The chassis temperature is extreme. The appliance hasinitiated a shutdown to protect itself. The operatingenvironment should be monitored and corrected beforerestarting the appliance.

chassisTemperatureWarning.desc: The chassis temperature is either too high or too low.The temperature should be monitored and, if possible, corrected.

chassisTemperatureUnknown.desc: The chassis temperature is unknown, because reading can't beobtained from the chassis temperature sensor.

chassisCPUFanStopped.desc: One or more CPU fans have stopped. The appliancehas initiated a shutdown to protect itself. A newmotherboard may be required to correct the fan.Contact Network Appliance for direction.

chassisCPUFanSlow.desc: A CPU fan is spinning too slowly. A new motherboardmay be required to correct the fan. Contact NetworkAppliance for direction.

chassisCPUFanOk.desc: All CPU fan(s) are properly functioning.

chassisPowerSupplyDegraded.desc: One or more chassis power supplies are degraded.A description of the degraded state has beenlogged to the console and message log file.

chassisPowerSupplyRemoved.desc: One or more chassis power supplies are removed.

chassisPowerSupplyOff.desc: One or more chassis power supplies are off.

chassisPowerSuppliesOk.desc: The chassis power supplies are all functioning properly.

chassisPowerSupplyOk.desc: This chassis power supply is functioning properly.

chassisPowerDegraded.desc: The power within the chassis is degraded.A description of the degraded state has beenlogged to the console and message log file.

chassisPowerOk.desc: The power within the chassis is functioning properly.

chassisFanDegraded.desc: A chassis fan has been degraded.

chassisFanRemoved.desc: A chassis fan FRU has been removed.

chassisFanStopped.desc: One or more chassis fans have stopped.

chassisFanWarning.desc: One or more chassis fans is spinning slowly or too fast.

chassisFanOk.desc: All chassis fans are functioning properly.

writeVerificationFailed.desc: A write has failed a verification teston a SnapValidator enabled volume.

domainControllerDisconnect.desc: A CIFS domain controller connection to the filer has failed.

dcPasswdChangeFailed.desc: An attempt to change the filer's password with the domaincontroller has failed.

domainControllerConnected.desc: A CIFS domain controller connection to the filer has beenestablished.

plexFailed.desc: This trap is issued when one plex of a mirroredtraditional volume or aggregate is failed. The stringsent with this trap specifies name of affected plex ormirrored traditional volume or aggregate.

plexOffline.desc: This trap is issued when a plex becomes offline.The string sent with this trap specifies name ofaffected plex or mirrored traditional volume or aggregate.

shelfSESElectronicsFailed.desc: One or more of the enclosure services devices in adisk shelf has failed. Some shelf designs combinethe enclosure monitoring hardware function into themodule that provides the storage interface tothe shelf. A failure in the enclosure monitoringsection of these combined modules does not necessarilyindicate a failure in disk or loop or bus operation,which may be able to continue.

shelfSESElectronicsInfo.desc: A previously reported failure of an enclosureservices device in a disk shelf has been corrected,or the device has reported information that does notnecessarily require customer action.

shelfIFModuleFailed.desc: One or more of the storage interface modules in adisk shelf has failed. Some shelf designs combine theenclosure monitoring hardware function into the modulethat operates the fibre channel loop or SCSI in theshelf. This failure is of the storage interfaceitself, not a failure of the enclosure monitoring,which may be able to continue. This failure may makeone or more disks in the shelf or in the loop or busunavailable.

shelfIFModuleWarning.desc: One or more of the storage interface modules in adisk shelf has a warning condition. Some shelf designs combine theenclosure monitoring hardware function into the modulethat operates the fibre channel loop or SCSI in theshelf. This warning condition is of the storage interfaceitself, not a failure of the enclosure monitoring,which may be able to continue.

shelfIFModuleInfo.desc: A previously reported failure of a disk shelfinterface module has been corrected, or the module hasreported information that does not necessarily requirecustomer action.

maxDirSizeAlert.desc: A directory has reached it's maxdirsize limit. Eitherincrease the maxdirsize or clean up the directory.

maxDirSizeWarning.desc: A directory is getting close to it's maxdirsize limit. Eitherincrease the maxdirsize or clean up the directory.

cifsStatsExhaustMemCtrlBlk.desc: A request for a CIFS control block can not be granted. Allcontrol blocks are in use.

chassisPSRemovedxMinShutdown.desc: Power Supply Unit is removed from the system. System willbe shutdown in x minutes if it is not put back.

chassisPSUsMismatch.desc: Power Supply Units in the system are of different type.Please replace them with correct Power Supply Units.

chassisFanFailxMinShutdown.desc: Multiple chassis fan failure. System willshut down in a few minutes if not corrected.

chassisPSUwrongInput.desc: Power Supply Unit (PSU) in the system is connected to anincompatible external power source. Please changethe power source being used or replace the PSUwith one that matches the current power source.

powerSupplyFanFailxMinShutdown.desc: Multiple power supply fans failure.System will shut down in a few minutes if not corrected.

remoteSystemMgtAlert.desc: system remote management detected a system down event.The trap includes a string describing the specific eventwhich triggered the trap. The string is structured in thefollowing form:Remote Management Event: type={system_down|system_up|test|keep_alive},severity={alert|warning|notice|normal|debug|info},event={post_error|watchdog_reset|power_loss|abnormal_reboot},key=valueAn example of a complete message would be:Remote Management Event: type=system_down, severity=alert,event=watchdog_reset, ss=16bytesAdditional key=value items may, in the future, be appendedto this message.The events that would generate this trap would be:post_error: Fatal POST error on bootpower_loss: Loss of power to systemabnormal_reboot:l2_watchdog_reset

remoteSystemMgmtWarning.desc: system remote management detected a system down event.The trap includes a string describing the specific eventwhich triggered the trap. The string is structured in thefollowing form:Remote Management Event: type={system_down|system_up|test|keep_alive},severity={alert|warning|notice|normal|debug|info},event={loss-of-heartbeat},key=valueAn example of a complete message would be:Remote Management Event: type=system_down, severity=warning,event=loss_of_heartbeat, ss=16bytesAdditional key=value items may, in the future, be appendedto this message.The events that would generate this trap would be:loss_of_heartbeat: Loss of heartbeat to the RLM.

remoteSystemMgmtNotification.desc: system remote management detected a system down event.The trap includes a string describing the specific eventwhich triggered the trap. The string is structured in thefollowing form:Remote Management Event: type={system_down|system_up|test|keep_alive},severity={alert|warning|notice|normal|debug|info},event={power_off_via_rlm,power_cycle_via_rlm,reset_via_rlm},key=valueAn example of a complete message would be:Remote Management Event: type=system_down, severity=notice,event=power_off_via_rlm, ss=16bytesAdditional key=value items may, in the future, be appendedto this message.The events that would generate this trap would be:power_off_via_rlm: This indicates system power offpower_cycle_via_rlm: This indicates system power cyclereset_via_rlm: This indicates system reset.

remoteSystemMgmtPeriodic.desc: This is a periodic keep alive from system remote management.The trap includes a string describing the specific eventwhich triggered the trap. The string is structured in thefollowing form:Remote Management Event: type={system_down|system_up|test|keep_alive},severity={alert|warning|notice|normal|debug|info},event={periodic_message}An example of a complete message would be:Remote Management Event: type=keep_alive, severity=info,event=periodic_messageAdditional key=value items may, in the future, be appendedto this message.

remotesystemMgmtTest.desc: This is a test trap from system remote management.The trap includes a string describing the specific eventwhich triggered the trap. The string is structured in thefollowing form:Remote Management Event: type={system_down|system_up|test|keep_alive},severity={alert|warning|notice|normal|debug|info},event={periodic_message}An example of a complete message would be:Remote Management Event: type=test, severity=notice, event=testAdditional key=value items may, in the future, be appendedto this message.

diskMultipathOneSwitch.desc: A multipathed disk is only connected to one switch.

diskMultipathNoTakeover.desc: Multipath disks or luns could not be detected for the partner.The node will be unable to takeover correctly.

diskMultipathWarning.desc: Synchronous mirroring is enabled, even though disks are notmultipathed.

driveDisableErr.desc: A drive has been disabled by the shelf module due tohardware errors. If it is the only drive in the shelfthat is disabled, replace the drive.

hbaOfflineInformation.desc: A host bus adapter (HBA) port has been disabled.This state may be caused either by user command or byerrors that make the interface unable to communicatewith attached devices.
